<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Database Reset Not Allowed - Ethiopian Vote System</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
  <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/reset_error.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="error-container">
      <div class="error-icon">
        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
      </div>
      <h2 class="error-title">Database Reset Not Allowed</h2>

      <div class="warning-box">
        <h5><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Voting Period is Currently Active</h5>
        <p>The database reset feature is disabled while the voting period is open to protect the integrity of the election data.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>All voters are currently able to cast their votes</li>
          <li>Resetting the database would delete all votes and voter data</li>
          <li>This action is only permitted when voting is closed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p class="error-message">
        To perform a database reset, you must first close the voting period using the "Set Election Period" feature.
        Once the voting period is closed, you can safely reset the database.
      </p>

      <a href="/admin/login" class="btn-primary">
        <i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Admin Panel
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
